summary:
Politics, economics, culture, history, and language all have been combined to form the basis of my studies and my perspective on the world. For me, nothing is more interesting than discussing past and current affairs with others. 
I have spent the past years submerging myself in East Asia, and specifically Korea and Japan, in order to further my knowledge of the region and find out what drives people, both those from the region and outside of it.
